                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus target="#27rb">27rb</locus>: short
                        coloured (red, black, white) ornamental band; geometric motifs
                        (interlaces).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">- <locus target="#51rb">51rb</locus>: short
                        coloured (red, black, white) ornamental band; floral motifs (?).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">- <locus target="#57ra">57ra</locus>: short
                        coloured (red, black, white) ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">- <locus target="#60ra">60ra</locus>: short
                        coloured (red, black, white) ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">- <locus target="#70va">70va</locus>: short
                        coloured (red, black, white) ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Notes in the upper margin, written in a crude
                              secondary hand, referring to the content of the Ms.: fols. 13r, 14r,
                              21r, 21v, 27r, 31v, 54v, 57r, 58r, 67v, 70v, 73v, 76v, 77r. - Threads
                              have been inserted in the upper corner/outer margins of fols. 14, 27,
                              51, 57, 70, 77, 88, 91.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- The names of the angels are written in a crude secondary hand on <locus target="#115ra">fol.  115ra</locus>. - Two names (perhaps later owners/donors) are written in a crude secondary hand in blue ballpoint pen on <locus target="#115v">fol.  115v</locus>: priest (qes) Gäbrä Śǝllase and ʾabba Yoḥannǝs (?). - Corrections written over erasures: e.g., fols. 4ra, 36rb, 53rb, 78ra, 86vb, 102rb. - Omitted letters or words written interlineally: e.g., fols. 3rb, 54va, 62va, 65rab, 92ra, 107va. - The word እገሌ is marked above and below by a series of dashes written in red ink: fols. 61vab, 62ra. - The scribe used compressed script: e.g., fols. 45vb-46va, 50vb-51rb. - Scribbles and doodles: fols. 3r, 4r.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with reddish-brown leather;
                           textile inlays.
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
